    {
      "name": "2. Token Operations",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "UserInfo - Get User Claims",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response contains sub claim', function () {",
                  "    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('sub');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response matches JWT token claims', function () {",
                  "    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    // UserInfo response should contain user claims from JWT token",
                  "    // (excluding protected claims like iss, aud, exp, iat, jti, typ, scope)",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.be.an('object');",
                  "    ",
                  "    // Common user claims that should be present",
                  "    if (pm.environment.get('access_token')) {",
                  "        console.log('Access token available - UserInfo claims should match decoded JWT');",
                  "    }",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// Log response for debugging",
                  "var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "console.log('UserInfo Response:', JSON.stringify(jsonData, null, 2));",
                  "console.log('Note: This response should match the claims in your decoded JWT token (from jwt.io)');"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}",
                "description": "Access token from Step 2: Exchange Code for Tokens"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/realms/{{realm}}/protocol/openid-connect/userinfo",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "auth",
                "realms",
                "{{realm}}",
                "protocol",
                "openid-connect",
                "userinfo"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Get user information (claims) using access token.\n\n**Important:** The response from this endpoint will match exactly with the claims in your decoded JWT access token (from Step 2: Exchange Code for Tokens).\n\n**Protected claims excluded:** `iss`, `aud`, `exp`, `iat`, `jti`, `auth_time`, `nonce`, `acr`, `azp`, `typ`, `scope`\n\n**Example Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"sub\": \"34144\",\n  \"name\": \"FARIZ NASIRUDIN\",\n  \"given_name\": \"FARIZ\",\n  \"family_name\": \"NASIRUDIN\",\n  \"preferred_username\": \"fariz\",\n  \"email\": \"fariz\",\n  \"email_verified\": true\n}\n```\n\nTo verify: Decode your access token at https://jwt.io and compare the claims with this response."
          }
        },
